5:
Heh. By the looks of it, you're holding
down the fort pretty well, aren't you?
9:
Yep! I've got some extra hands to go
around, and the number of guests
has dropped to more manageable
levels!
12:
All in all, we're doing good. Maybe
even too good...
15:
I've got this weird feeling that it's... a
bit too quiet? Too slow? Maybe even
too comfortable? I don't know.
19:
Poor thing. Overexposure to danger
must have numbed your senses.
Would you like me to introduce a
little to the mix?
29: All right then. How 'bout a drink?
32:
You only had a lil' sip during the last
festival. Take a load off, chug a few
cold ones, and blow off some steam!
36:
Drinks? Well... Sure, I guess. I can
trust you, Taichi.
40:
Let's do it. Nothing wrong with a little
bit of self-indulgence from time to
time!
53:
Now, now! No need to make a fuss,
Alk. Just one drink, that's all I ask!
One teeny tiny little drink. What
could go wrong?
57:
Hahaha! Precisely, my good man!
It's high time you took the next step
forward into adulthood. Perhaps
some of the ladies here can teach
you more about that—
61:
No, no, fair is fair. We promised him
JUST drinks, and that's what we'll do.
This is the perfect place to do
it—fewer pryin' eyes, if you know
what I mean.
63:
Let's have ourselves a lil' boys' night,
eh? We can, uh, skip on the pretty
ladies. Just for tonight.
67:
Don't look so glum, Alk! Wouldn't
want to disrespect the lovely Miss
Kikuno now, would you? She was
delighted to hear that you would be
visiting.
74:
Hng... I mean... I guess I don't HATE
the idea of being here...
80:
Here we go. This is perfect. Just keep
an open mind, relax, and we'll have
a nice pleasant evening over drinks.
Sounds fun, right?
87:
*sigh* Just... let me go to the
bathroom first.
91:
I have to admit, it's a pretty
impressive place. I'd be lying if I said
I wasn't a bit curious...
94:
...No! Curiosity's dangerous. It's times
like these, a guy's gotta be on alert.
Stay in line. Trust nobody, not even...
103: The toilet is that way, Sir.
110:
Whoa! What's with that look on your
face? Something crazy go down in
that bathroom, or what?
114:
Nope. I just... feel like, you know.
Burying my head in the sand forever.
118:
After a few more rounds, could we
maybe... drink somewhere else?
That wouldn't be rude, right?
128:
I can't believe my luck... Of all the
times to run into her, why THEN?!
133:
Sorry 'bout that, pal... But say, that
girl... You said her name was Elise?
I've never heard you talk about her
before.
137:
N-no, it's just... I like her, but she's not
someone I would ever... pursue.
141:
Which implies the existence of
someone who you WOULD pursue?
Perhaps multiple ladies? Heh.
146:
GAH—I'm not here to talk about
relationships, okay?!
150:
Serves me right for trying to talk to
anyone around here... You're all
wasted!
154:
Don't sweat it, Alk. You're not likely to
get much good advice from a
bunch of drunkards anyway.
159:
Yeah. Might have better luck talking
to people who know better—like
your parents, for example. They're
respectable people, right?
164: Well, yeah. I suppose they are.
168:
Then what are you waiting for? Talk
to them already—while you still have
the chance.
172:
Hmm... Yeah, I guess there's no point
in being embarrassed about it...
177:
Can you believe it, Nanami? An
invitation from our own son!
181:
Your father has been dying to visit
the restaurant, but he didn't want to
bother you. Isn't that right, Kenichi?
186:
I mean, you don't have to worry
about bothering me...
190:
So? What is it you wanted to talk
about, dear?
194:
It's nothing serious, really. I just
wanted to ask...
198:
...How did you figure out what you
wanted to do? Like, career-wise?
201:
I've had a lot of spare time lately,
and there's so much I want to try
out, but... I feel like I'm all over the
place.
203:
I wouldn't say this in front of others,
but... sometimes I feel like I have too
many options.
207:
I get it. It's the paradox of
choice—the more options available
to you, the more stressful it is to
choose.
211:
Yeah... I think I'm just being too
indecisive. That's why I wanted to
ask you two.
215:
That's a tough one, honey. I have a
feeling my case won't be very
helpful. For me, it was just a process
of elimination.
221:
And me? I basically just went with
the flow—I don't remember making
any "big" decision really.
225:
What? But... you guys worked so
hard, I figured you'd have a whole
elaborate reason for picking your
jobs...
229:
Not really. And what's more, we're in
the same boat as you now! I had to
restart my whole career.
232:
I just got lucky and managed to find
a job at The Oculus! Well, I guess
that IS technically a choice that I
had to make. Hmm.
237:
Just focus on what's most important
to you—the stuff you're not willing to
give up on. The rest? Well... I'm sure
you'll handle it.
245: Because you're our son, of course!
250:
Not to mention, I hear you saved the
world.
255:
...Thanks. I don't know if I've found my
answer yet, but I feel better.
259:
That's good to hear. But we're not
done talking yet, Ayumu.
264:
We need to talk about your sister
Nao.
271:
What in the world is that girl doing?
She hasn't explained herself at all!
She even told us that you died,
whatever that means. Can you
believe it?
276:
Wait... She seriously didn't fill you in?
And now you're asking ME to tell you?
281:
We aren't leaving until you give us a
proper explanation, young man.
286:
Okay, but... promise you won't freak
out, all right? It's a long story, and
you might find it kind of hard to
believe.
